<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5033216>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Fig. 3.—Current known distribution of Microtus cabrerae in Portugal and Spain (each green dot represents occurrence records of the species mapped at a 10- by 10-km resolution), following Fernández-Salvador (2007b) and Mira et al. (2008), updated with records from local studies (e.g., Rosário and Mathias 2007; Garrido-Garcıá et al. 2008, 2013; Ortuño 2009; Pita et al. 2010; and the database from the Conservation Biology Unit, University of Évora). Major rivers (blue lines) and mountain ranges (gray scale) across the Iberian Peninsula also are represented." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/5033216/files/figure.png" .

